snippet: Egypt’s new military-led government enlisted internationally recognized figures to serve as its public face and promised quick elections, but a transitional plan was widely derided as authoritarian and rushed.
abstract: Egypt’s new military-led government enlisted internationally recognized figures to serve as its public face and promises quick elections, but transitional plan is widely derided across political spectrum as authoritarian and rushed.

byline.contributor: Sarah Mousa contributed reporting from Cairo, and Rick Gladstone from New York.

lead_paragraph: Egypt’s new military-led government enlisted internationally recognized figures to serve as its public face and promised quick elections, but a transitional plan was widely derided as authoritarian and rushed.

headline.main: Egypt Leaders’ Transition Plan Meets With Swift Criticism
